In [116]:
#It calculates the average salary for each job title
_average_salary_of_job = salary_.groupby('job_title')['salary_in_usd'].mean()


#this code finds the job with the highest salary
highest_job_salary = _average_salary_of_job.idxmax()

# Creates a bar graph
plt.figure(figsize=(30, 8))
_average_salary_of_job.plot(kind='bar',color='blue')
plt.xlabel('Job Title')
plt.ylabel('Salary (USD)')
plt.title('Jobs with the Highest Salary')
plt.show()
print("The job with the highest_job_salary is:", highest_job_salary)

The job with the highest_job_salary is: Data Science Tech Lead
